Must run with python version 3.

files:
 reliable_getMeteo_config.py
 reliable_getMeteo.py

default run:
 python reliable_getMeteo.py

 The script creates a file in JSON format with downloaded forecast data from http://meteo.tecnico.ulisboa.pt
 All configurations are in reliable_getMeteo_config.py


 Examples:
  ## get help
  python reliable_getMeteo.py -h

  ## output on screen
  python reliable_getMeteo.py -o

  ## output on file with verbose
  python reliable_getMeteo.py -vv

  ## output on file with no verbose
  python reliable_getMeteo.py -nv
